      .question
        a(href="#").title
          | What is the Blocktix system?
          i.icon_chevron-right
        .answer
          | The Blocktix System is a platform that replaces the current fragmented
          | markets of event ticket distribution, ticket transfer and event promotion.
          | Blocktix is a single system for all services and provides a low overhead
          | for distributors and promoters, freeing up money otherwise wasted in
          | inefficient market-based systems.
      .question
        a(href="#").title
          | Why is there a need for Blocktix?
          i.icon_chevron-right
        .answer
          | Event hosting is an expansive and growing market, yet much like the
          | financial industry, it suffers from constant, systemic challenges
          | regarding fraud prevention, transfers of ownership and intermediary
          | cost. Event hosts use a series of costly, legacy services to provide a
          | solution for these challenges.
          ul
            li
              | Ticket distribution services (Ticketmaster, Eventbrite) are used
              | to simplify the ticketing process and to protect against fraud. The
              | associated surcharge for these distribution services can be up to
              | 15% of the ticket value.
            li
              | Intermediary services such as Stubhub are used in the p2p
              | secondary market to combat fraud and counterfeiting losses.
              | Industry wide, fraud losses exceed $1 billion annually. Many
              | P2P transfer intermediaries charge excessive fees to both
              | buyers and sellers.
            li
              | A variety of advertising mediums and services are used to sell
              | available tickets to an event. Advertising costs for an event
              | regularly exceeds 20% of the event's overall budget.
              | Utilizing Ethereum smart contracts, Blocktix offers a near perfect
              | solution to many of the current challenges facing event hosting
              | businesses.
